name: js/camera.js
Camera
description: provides easy functions to take images, sets up a video and canvas element

params.name: width
params.description: width in pixels for the video element

name: setResolution
description: sets the resolution of both video and canvas element, so that no distortion happens.

return.description: Object with attributes width and height, calculated.

name: takeImage
description: takes an image by drawing the video element's content on the canvas.

return.description: the canvas element (can be used to access functions such as .toBlob())

name: js/faceapi.js
FaceAPI
description:
Used for accessing Microsoft's Face API. Written for general use cases,
not specifically for this application.

name: makeRequest
description: makes a request to the API, used for simplifying.

params.name: method
params.description: Method to use for request, e.g. GET, POST, PUT, etc.

params.name: isImage
params.description: If an image is in the body

name: createPersonGroup
description: creates a personGroup with name identical to the id.

name: getPersonGroupOrCreate
description: checks if personGroup exists and if it doesn't, creates it.

name: addPersonFace
description: add a PersonFace to a Person

name: listPersons
description: lists all Persons of a PersonGroup

name: js/main.js
checkKey
description:
Checks whether the key is set.
This is a very simple error handler, I would've liked to expand it to also
check for other errors.

name: setupPersonGroup
description:
Here we're setting up the personGroup.
I opted to use one personGroup for each user, as we don't need mulitple for
the use case specified. We save the id in the localStorage for persistence.
The FaceAPI does support multiple personGroups.
